greatest index where character
`c` has appeared so far."];
claim [shape=box style="rounded,filled" fillcolor="#DCFCE7" color="#94A3B8" penwidth=1.2 margin="0.18,0.12" fontname="Helvetica" fontsize=12 label="Window Repair Lemma
When processing character
`s[r]`, if its previous
occurrence is at index `p =
last[s[r]]`, then every valid
..."];
action [shape=box style="rounded,filled" fillcolor="#FDE68A" color="#94A3B8" penwidth=1.2 margin="0.18,0.12" fontname="Helvetica" fontsize=12 label="Algorithm Consequence
Scan `s` once from left to
right."];
proof [shape=box style="rounded,filled" fillcolor="#FCE7F3" color="#94A3B8" penwidth=1.2 margin="0.18,0.12" fontname="Helvetica" fontsize=12 label="Why It Works
Initially the window is empty,
so the valid-window invariant
holds vacuously."];
top -> state [style=invis];
state -> claim [label="sets up"];
claim -> action [label="justifies"];
